    <h2 id="company-overview">1. Western Refrigeration Company Overview</h2>
    <p>Western Refrigeration Pvt. Ltd. is an Indian manufacturer of commercial and industrial refrigeration products. The company was founded in the early 1980s and is headquartered in Ahmedabad, Gujarat — a state that has become a hub for refrigeration manufacturing in India. Over the past four decades, Western has grown from a small regional player into a nationally recognized brand with products installed in hundreds of thousands of commercial establishments across India.</p>

    <p>The company manufactures a wide range of cooling equipment: visi coolers, deep freezers, chest coolers, water coolers, bottle coolers, display counters, and cold rooms. Their core strength lies in affordability and tropicalized design — Western products are engineered for the Indian climate, where ambient temperatures routinely cross 40°C and power supply can be inconsistent.</p>

    <p>Western operates one of the largest commercial refrigeration manufacturing facilities in western India. Their production lines are ISO certified, and they use a combination of Indian-made and imported compressors (primarily Tecumseh and Embraco) depending on the product line and capacity. The brand distributes through a network of authorized dealers, distributors, and channel partners spread across all major Indian states.</p>

    <p>One of the reasons Western has a strong market presence in India is its pricing strategy. The brand positions itself firmly in the budget-to-mid-range segment, making commercial refrigeration accessible to small and medium businesses — from a neighbourhood kirana store to a mid-sized bakery or restaurant chain. If you are comparing options for your <a href="/blog/commercial-refrigerator-guide">commercial refrigerator guide</a>, Western deserves a place on your shortlist for value-oriented purchases.</p>

    <h3>Key Company Facts</h3>
    <ul>
