    <h2 id="deep-freezers">4. Deep Freezers — Models & Prices 2026</h2>
    <p>Deep freezers are Western Refrigeration's second-largest product category. These are chest-style or top-opening freezers designed to store frozen goods at temperatures between -18°C and -24°C. Bakeries use them for frozen dough, butter stocks, ice cream, and frozen fruit purees. Restaurants rely on them for frozen meats, seafood, and pre-prepared items. Ice cream parlours and sweet shops use them as the primary storage and sometimes even as serving freezers.</p>

    <p>Western deep freezers come in two main lid types: hard top (solid insulated lid) and glass top (transparent lid for retail display). Hard top models are more energy efficient and are preferred for back-of-house storage, while glass top models work better in customer-facing locations.</p>

