    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions — Western Refrigeration India</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>1. Is Western Refrigeration a good brand in India?</h3>
      <p>Western Refrigeration is a reputable Indian brand with over 40 years of manufacturing experience. It is particularly strong in the budget-to-mid-range segment. For price-sensitive businesses, Western offers reliable performance at 15-30% lower cost than premium brands like Blue Star and Voltas. The brand is best suited for businesses in western and northern India where dealer and service coverage is strongest. For premium applications or regions with limited Western service presence, consider Blue Star, Voltas, or Godrej as alternatives.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>2. What is the price of a Western visi cooler in India?</h3>
      <p>Western visi cooler prices in India range from ₹18,000 for a basic 100L single-door model to ₹80,000 for a 1200L triple-door unit. The most popular models for small businesses — 200L to 400L single-door — cost between ₹22,000 and ₹42,000. Double-door models (500-700L) range from ₹42,000 to ₹62,000. Prices vary by dealer, region, and ongoing promotions. GST at 18% is typically additional.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>3. How does Western compare with Blue Star for commercial refrigeration?</h3>
      <p>Blue Star is generally considered superior to Western in build quality, energy efficiency, and after-sales service. Blue Star products cost 20-35% more than comparable Western models. If budget is your primary constraint, Western delivers good functional performance at a lower price. If you can invest more upfront and want better long-term reliability, lower running costs, and stronger service support nationwide, Blue Star is the better choice. The gap is most noticeable in build quality and noise levels.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>4. What is the warranty on Western refrigeration products?</h3>
      <p>Western Refrigeration typically offers a 1-year comprehensive warranty on all products, covering parts and labour. The compressor carries a separate warranty of 4 to 5 years depending on the product line. Extended warranty options are available through authorized dealers at an additional cost of approximately ₹2,000 to ₹5,000 per year. Always ensure your warranty is registered directly with Western and not just through the dealer.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>5. Which Western deep freezer is best for a bakery?</h3>
      <p>For a small to medium bakery, the 300L Hard Top Deep Freezer (₹24,000–32,000) is the most popular choice. It provides enough space for frozen dough, butter stocks, frozen fruit purees, and ice cream inventory without taking up excessive floor space. If you run a larger bakery with significant frozen storage needs — bulk butter, multiple frozen dough varieties, and frozen cake bases — consider the 500L model (₹38,000–48,000). Glass-top models are only necessary if the freezer is in a customer-facing location, such as an ice cream serving counter.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>6. Where can I buy Western refrigeration products online?</h3>
      <p>Western Refrigeration products are available online through IndiaMART (the most common B2B platform with multiple dealer listings), Amazon India, and Flipkart (for select models). You can also contact Western directly through their official website to find the nearest authorized dealer. For the best combination of price, warranty, and after-sales support, we recommend buying through an authorized dealer rather than unverified online sellers. At <a href="/">BakeDesk</a>, we can connect you with verified Western dealers and help you compare prices across channels.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>7. Is Western Refrigeration good for ice cream storage?</h3>
      <p>Yes, Western deep freezers are widely used for ice cream storage across India. Their hard-top deep freezers maintain temperatures down to -24°C, which is suitable for ice cream storage (typically requires -18°C to -22°C). The glass-top variants are popular with ice cream parlours for customer-facing display. For a dedicated ice cream business, consider the 400L or 500L models to ensure adequate storage capacity during peak summer demand. The key advantage of Western for ice cream storage is their wide voltage tolerance — the freezer will continue to maintain temperature even during power fluctuations.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>8. How much electricity does a Western visi cooler consume?</h3>
      <p>Power consumption of a Western visi cooler depends on the capacity and ambient temperature. A 200L single-door model typically consumes 2-3 units (kWh) per day in moderate conditions and 3-4 units per day during peak summer. A 500L model consumes 4-6 units per day. A triple-door 1200L unit can consume 7-10 units per day. At an average electricity rate of ₹8 per unit, monthly running costs range from approximately ₹500 for a small unit to ₹2,400 for a large triple-door visi cooler.</p>
    </div>

